{
  "stem": "5758.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think three months after-- March, April, May, maybe-- maybe June-- the law came out that Jewish students couldn't be educated anymore, but they had to learn a trade.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when-- my parents entered me into a tailoring school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My oldest brother, who was studying in university-- he was studying medicine at that time-- he could not continue anymore.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My middle brother could not continue his education.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it was extremely difficult for us Jews to go out in the street and-- and maybe do whatever we wanted to do.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because at that time, right after the invasion, at the time when Schuschnigg was actually in power, a lot of left-wing slogans were painted all over the pavement, all over the walls.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Placards were posted up, anti-Nazi, especially in our neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember that the SR picked up people from the street in order to clean the slogans, communist or socialist slogans, from the street.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were always afraid to-- to be part of it, to be asked to-- to clean.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One day I did go.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had to go out to get something, to a shop, and I saw a group of people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Curious as I am, I went there to have a look what's-- what's there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was an-- I'll never forget it-- there was an very old Jew with a beard.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I think he must have been somewhere around 60 or 70 years of age.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they gave him-- they gave him water and a toothbrush, and he had to clean the slogan with a toothbrush.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it wasn't good enough, and they kicked him while he did it.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
